[02:35.40]Neville Cardus, who wrote for the Manchester Guardian
[02:39.49]from 1917 until shortly before his death in 1975,
[02:45.18]is now known solely as a writer of essays on the game of cricket.
[02:51.15]During his lifetime, though, he was also one of England¡¯s foremost classical-music critics,
[02:58.54]and a stylist so widely admired that his Autobiography£¨1947£©became a best-seller.
[03:07.58]He was knighted in 1967, the first music critic to be so honored.
[03:13.46]Yet only one of his books is now in print,
[03:17.95]and his vast body of writings on music is unknown save to specialists.
[03:24.68]Is there any chance that Cardus¡¯s criticism will enjoy a revival?
